        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 2:59PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>The combination of accumulating dry fuels, low relative humidity
down near 30 percent and gusty winds up to near 20 mph will
continue to lead to increased fire danger into this evening.
</description>
        <instruction>A burn ban remains in effect for for the area until further
notice. This also means all burning permits have been cancelled.
PLEASE, heed the burn ban in order to mitigate any additional
uncontained wildfires.</instruction>
